  "notes": "Luganda (Ganda), Bantu, Uganda. Standard orthography of 24 letters. <c> = /c/ and <j> = /ɟ/ (palatal stops, often realised [tʃ]/[dʒ]); <ny> = /ɲ/; <ŋ> = /ŋ/, commonly typed <ng'>; <ng> without the apostrophe is prenasalised /ŋɡ/. Long vowels are written double. /l/ and /r/ are one phoneme: <r> is written after <e> and <i>, <l> elsewhere. Consonant gemination and tone are phonemic; tone is not written and is not modelled here.",
